Title: A Girsanov type approach to filtering in a simple linear system driven by a fractional
Author: Alain Le Breton 
Keyword: Key Words and Phrases: Fractional Brownian motion; Girsanov formula; Optimal filtering; Innovation process.  
Note: AMS 1991 Subject Classification: Primary 60G35, 62M20; Secondary 60G15, 93E11.  
Address: B.P. 53 38041 Grenoble Cedex 09, France  
Affiliation: LMC/IMAG, Universite J. Fourier,  
Abstract: In Le Breton (1997) a direct approach based on the minimization of the mean square error of a linear estimate was developed to solve the problem of optimal filtering of a fixed random variable observed through a linear channel driven by a fractional Brownian motion with Hurst parameter H 2 (1=2; 1). The results were applied to determine the best linear estimator in a related parameter estimation problem and then a Girsanov type formula extending that given by Norros et al. (1996) was identified and proved. Here we take a reverse way to investigate a filtering problem similar to that mentioned above. At first a Girsanov type result for a fractional Brownian motion which extends slightly that of Le Breton (1997) is proposed. Then this result is applied to derive closed form expressions both for the optimal filter and the conditional variance of the filtering error in the considered model. Finally the properties of a process which plays here the role played by the innovation process in the usual situation where the observation noise is a Brownian motion are studied. 1. Introduction. Numerous theoritical results and successful applications have 
